br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 9:11:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> Ok, lets let everyone throw their cards out on the table...<br><br>Heres mine...<br><br>What I think we need/want:<br>1.  Serenity-for the love of god I go thru mana fast enough, give me the regen.<br>2.  Endurance Regen-Tie endurance regen to the regen chant, make it 1/2 as effective as the bards end regen, give the second skald in a group something to play.<br>3.  Fury of the Gods- Replace it, repair it so its something we should actually think about buying, or anything, but as it is now, its useless.<br><br>What I don't think we need.<br>1.  Medium shields-I never use them, they have no effect in increasing your blocking, so other than looks, they dont do anything for me.<br>2.  More HP's-With realm skills now we can easily get more HP's, at 50 before Realm Skills I'll have close to 1400 if not more, with realm skills I'll easily pass the 1500 mark.<br>3.  2x Spec and Shield Skill.  Love to have it, but it would greatly overpower us.  I could chase someone down shield stun them, nuke nuke, swing swing, mez, nuke nuke...and they'd be dead.  No offense, but if I wanted 2x Spec and a shield, I woulda played a Thane.  (Could never be a slow class again though)<br><br>Fact of the matter, in my personal opinion, we are pretty darn balanced as we are right now, could we use a few things, sure, who couldn't, but I don't see us near the top of the list of classes who are hurting or gimped in any way. <p><center><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Drav/fullsize/bankok_sig2.jpg" align=center></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ubankok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bankok</A> at: 5/8/02 9:20:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 10:17:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skalds...</span><hr size=1> Many consider Skalds over-powered. I think we are very solid. End regen is definately a problem in Midgard. I really dont see why Midgard DOESNT have it. <br><br>I would have liked to have seen Bladedance as an option for Skalds.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvivaxkithicor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vivax Kithicor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 10:30:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> Bankok, I largely agree.  Here's my version:<br><br>Need/want menu (&quot;menu&quot; because a subset of these should be chosen, not the entire list):<br>1.  Serenity<br>2.  Endurance regeneration added to Songs of Rest.  Either that or double the healing rates.<br>3.  Fixing/replacing Fury of the Gods with something useful.  Perhaps something designed for keep doors, for group endurance regen, for a resurrection ability, for group power regen.  Heck, maybe just add to it a significant percentage increase for critical-hitting for the group's non-magical attacks.<br>4.  Evade II<br>5.  1.75 points per level.  Mythic's assassin classes are proof that Mythic can now handle fractions.<br>6.  Equipment as well-suited to our class as many other classes enjoy.<br>7.  Changing Stunning Shout's name.  Many board whiners believe this to be a real stun.<br>8.  Removing/fixing our resist chants.  What a joke they currently are.<br><br>Don't need:<br>1.  medium shields<br>2.  more hp<br>3.  shield skill (unless we first get more points per level)<br>4.  changing our Stunning Shout into a real stun.<br><br><br>Addendum:  Many non-skalds look at our list on paper and think we're overpowered.  And many skalds under level 45 think we can tank.  But reality at level 50, where a significant percentage of players are, is different. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvivaxkithicor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vivax Kithicor</A> at: 5/8/02 10:32:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 10:52:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cableone.net/truggiero/smxumcard.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> One thing I forgot to mention. Ressurection. Midgards only two res classes are Healer/Shamans. Generally these two classes are near the bottom of the list of popularity. Spiritmasters claiming the fame of being dead last. Shamans and healer numbers arent much better. <br><br>However, Clerics and Paladins are generally the most popular classes in Albion. Druids and Bards also being fairly popular. <br><br>I see Midgard at a big disadvantage in terms of ressers in the battlefield. Not because we only have two rezzers. But because those two are generally considered the &quot;un-popular&quot; classes. <br><br>I think Skalds getting the ability to rez, could fill that gap. While I understand many skalds dont neccessarily want that skill(and the headache/power drain that comes along with it), I really thing Midgard as a realm could greatly benefit from a somewhat popular class having the ability to rez. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A> at: 5/8/02 10:52:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/urunnyb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RunnyB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/8/02 12:17:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> I agree completely with the original poster, and would like to add that it would be really nice if +batllesong items did something.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=etzel>Etzel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 6:09:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> Things we need/want<br><br>Song of rest - double the regen rate.<br>Rez - the realm NEED this (even if it will be a pain to us).<br>FotG - make this apply when swinging at keep doors.<br>FotG - possible alternative, scrap it completely and give us a timer based skill where all shouts/resists stack for say 1 minute.<br>Evade II.<br>A proper stun not a mez.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukabutojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KabutoJones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 7:37:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> why would a skald get a rez? what leads you to believe that they would have that sort of ability? that would make almost as much sense as giving it to a shadowblade. if any third class should rez it should be the spiritmaster. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kilgour>Kilgour</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 8:07:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> Skald and rez reasoning<br><br>There is a certain logic to making a skald the third rez class.  Look at shaman and healer spell lists and the skald lists match those more closely than the skald does any other class.  One could argue that a skald is like a fighter/cleric type (if you played DnD in the &quot;old days&quot;).  In that regard, it makes sense.<br><br>OTOH, spiritmasters are underdeveloped and giving them a necromantic power to raise dead also sense.   They need class help in this regard.  If SMs could rez then you would indeed see more of them. <p>Kilgour PeacefulDeth<Dark Requiem>37 Level Skald  Galahad</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukabutojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KabutoJones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 8:38:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> how is a skald in any way, shape or form clerical? because we get a song of rest that's essentially useless and can only be used when sitting down? sorry, i just don't follow the logic there =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uanappo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>anappo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 10:26:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> &gt; how is a skald in any way, shape or form clerical?<br><br>Not the point here. The role-play reasoning could be invented for pretty much everything.<br><br>The fact of the matter - Midgad is seriously low on ressers.<br><br>Goal: to increase the number of ressers in Midgard.<br><br>Possible methods of achieving the goal:<br><br>A. Give more people an incentive to play healers or shamen.<br><br>B. Give res capabilities to an additional class.<br><br>If Mythic goes route B, they will have to decide which class should have that res capability. Again, they have 2 choices:<br><br>B1. Mythic gives the res capability to a class that is already highly popular. This would bring up the numbers of ressers in Midgard immediately.<br><br>Possible candiate classes: Skalds, Thanes, Hunters, Shadowblades.<br><br>B2. Mythic gives res capabilty to a unpopular (gimp) class. This could result in more people choosing that class end would perhaps result in eventual build-up of res-capable chars in Midgard.<br><br>Possible candiate classes: Spiritmasters, Warriors.<br><br>---------------<br><br>Now, the game-world explanation of why exactly any of these classes sould be able to ressurrect dead people depends on one thing only - imagination stat of the Mythic employee who has to come up with it. It doesn’t have mo make any sense at all. Much of what is already in doesn’t. Could be a new shout for skalds, that is so loud it wakes up the dead. Could be mouth-to-mouth breathing combat style for warriors. Doesn’t matter as it’s completely irrelevant to the focus point here - Midgard does not have enough ressers.<br><br>Ottar<br>49, Prydwen<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukabutojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KabutoJones</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 1:50:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald Concerns..</span><hr size=1> sorry, i dont see any way or reason why a skald should get a rez. it makes no sense. its a bad idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uanappo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>anappo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/9/02 5:30:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fte